commit.message:
QA: fix return type of _get_library_paths

The tuple is not of a fixed length. We also have to explicitly declare
the type of the variable in the function, otherwise mypy infers it from
the first declaration (os_is_nt) where it is a one-element tuple,
causing mismatches in the other branches of the "if" statement.
See https://stackoverflow.com/a/52860650 and
https://mypy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/type_inference_and_annotations.html.

verification.payload:
tree 1b8f60f70e38e062f1595a6984d6f300e947af04
parent 75baf4f5d9896e56f0a739f73b7ff8561b1299eb
author Louis Sautier <sautier.louis@gmail.com> 1706926103 +0100
committer Louis Sautier <sautier.louis@gmail.com> 1707613359 +0100

QA: fix return type of _get_library_paths

The tuple is not of a fixed length. We also have to explicitly declare
the type of the variable in the function, otherwise mypy infers it from
the first declaration (os_is_nt) where it is a one-element tuple,
causing mismatches in the other branches of the "if" statement.
See https://stackoverflow.com/a/52860650 and
https://mypy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/type_inference_and_annotations.html.
